;; TUI React-style Renderer: Virtual Widget Tree + Direct-Write Buffer
;;
;; Phase 2 & 3 of the React/re-frame adoption plan for the TUI engine.
;; Phase 1 (memoized projections) is already implemented.

{:name "tui-react-renderer"
 :version "0.1.0"

 :description
 "Adopt React-style virtual widget tree diffing and direct-write rendering
  for the TUI engine. Eliminates redundant buffer allocation and achieves
  component-level dirty tracking. Two phases, implementable independently."

 :context
 {:current-architecture
  "The TUI engine uses an Elm architecture (model → update → view).
   The view function (view.clj → interpret.clj) takes the full model and
   produces a complete cell buffer (vector of vectors of {:char :fg :bg :bold?}).
   Layout primitives (split-v, split-h, box) each allocate their own sub-buffer
   via make-buffer, render into it, then blit (copy cell-by-cell) into a parent
   buffer. paint-screen! diffs the final buffer against the previous frame and
   writes changed cells to the Lanterna terminal.

   Phase 1 (DONE): Projections are memoized by input signals — when you press
   j/k, project-workflows returns cached data in 0.01ms instead of 1.6ms.
   But the buffer layer still rebuilds 5100+ cells per frame."

  :key-files
  ["components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/core.clj"
   "components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/layout/buffer.clj"
   "components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/layout/container.clj"
   "components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/layout/table.clj"
   "components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/screen/lanterna.clj"
   "components/tui-views/src/ai/miniforge/tui_views/view.clj"
   "components/tui-views/src/ai/miniforge/tui_views/view/interpret.clj"
   "components/tui-views/src/ai/miniforge/tui_views/view/project.clj"
   "components/tui-views/resources/config/tui/screens.edn"]}

 :phases
 [{:phase :phase-2
   :name "Virtual widget tree with component-level diffing"
   :description
   "Replace the current 'view returns cell buffer' contract with 'view returns
    widget tree'. The runtime diffs the tree and only re-renders widgets whose
    props changed. This is the React virtual DOM equivalent for the terminal."

   :tasks
   [{:task "Define widget tree data structure"
     :detail
     "Create a widget descriptor format. Each node is a map:
        {:type :split-v/:table/:text/:box/...
         :key  unique-id (for stable diffing)
         :props {...widget-specific data...}
         :children [...]}
      Props should use the MEMOIZED projection results directly so that
      identical? checks on props catch unchanged widgets.
      File: components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/vtree.clj"}

    {:task "Implement tree differ"
     :detail
     "Diff old-tree vs new-tree. For each node:
        - If (identical? old-node new-node) → skip entirely (fast path)
        - If same :key and :type but different :props → mark dirty, re-render
        - If :key mismatch → unmount old, mount new
      Output: list of dirty widget paths that need re-rendering.
      The differ should be O(tree-size) in the worst case but O(1) for
      unchanged subtrees thanks to identical? checks on memoized data.
      File: components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/vtree.clj"}

    {:task "Add render cache per widget"
     :detail
     "Each widget node caches its last rendered cell buffer region.
      When a widget is clean (props identical?), its cached buffer region
      is reused without calling any render function. Store cache in an
      atom keyed by widget :key.
      File: components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/vtree.clj"}

    {:task "Update interpret.clj to return widget tree instead of cell buffer"
     :detail
     "Change interpret-node to return widget descriptors instead of calling
      layout primitives directly. The screen spec walker becomes:
        screens.edn → interpret (returns vtree) → differ → selective render
      Keep backward compatibility: if no vtree support, fall back to
      current buffer rendering.
      File: components/tui-views/src/ai/miniforge/tui_views/view/interpret.clj"}

    {:task "Update core.clj do-render! to use tree differ"
     :detail
     "Change do-render! flow:
        1. Call view-fn → get new widget tree
        2. Diff against cached previous tree
        3. For dirty widgets only: call their render fn → get cell regions
        4. Composite dirty regions into the frame buffer
        5. paint-screen! diffs the frame buffer (unchanged cells = no-op)
      File: components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/core.clj"}

    {:task "Wire overlay pipeline into widget tree"
     :detail
     "Overlays (command bar, help, completions, confirm dialog) should be
      widget tree nodes too, so they get the same dirty tracking. When the
      overlay hasn't changed, skip its render entirely.
      File: components/tui-views/src/ai/miniforge/tui_views/view.clj"}]

   :acceptance-criteria
   ["Pressing j/k on the workflow list only re-renders the table widget, not the tab bar or footer"
    "Switching views re-renders everything (clean behavior)"
    "All 250 existing tests pass without modification"
    "Overlay rendering (command bar, help) is skipped when not active"
    "Benchmark: j/k navigation renders in <5ms for 55 workflows on a 170x30 terminal"]}

  {:phase :phase-3
   :name "Direct-write renderer (eliminate intermediate buffers)"
   :description
   "Replace the allocate-then-blit pattern with direct writes into a single
    target buffer. Each widget renders with offset coordinates instead of
    allocating its own sub-buffer. Eliminates ~80% of buffer allocations."

   :tasks
   [{:task "Create RenderTarget abstraction"
     :detail
     "A mutable render target that widgets write into directly:
        (defprotocol IRenderTarget
          (put-string! [this x y text style])
          (get-cell [this x y])
          (sub-region [this x y w h]))
      sub-region returns a view into the same backing store with offset
      coordinates, NOT a new buffer. Use a Java 2D array backing store
      for O(1) random access.
      File: components/tui-engine/src/ai/miniforge/tui_engine/render_target.clj"}

    {:task "Port layout primitives to RenderTarget"
     :detail
     "Change split-v, split-h, box to accept a RenderTarget + region bounds
      instead of [cols rows] and returning a buffer. They call sub-region
      to get offset views and pass them to children.

      Before: (split-v [cols rows] ratio top-fn bottom-fn) → buffer
      After:  (split-v! target x y cols rows ratio top-fn bottom-fn) → nil

      Keep the old buffer-based API as a compatibility shim that creates
      a RenderTarget, renders into it, then extracts the buffer.
      Files: container.clj, table.clj, buffer.clj"}

    {:task "Port widget renderers to RenderTarget"
     :detail
     "Update render-table-widget, render-tree-widget, render-kanban-widget
      to write directly into a RenderTarget region instead of creating
      intermediate buffers. The table renderer is the highest priority —
      it's the most-rendered widget.
      File: interpret.clj, table.clj"}

    {:task "Update paint-screen! for RenderTarget"
     :detail
     "paint-screen! should diff the RenderTarget's backing array directly
      against the previous frame's array. Array element access is O(1)
      vs get-in on nested vectors. Store prev-frame as a plain 2D array.
      File: core.clj"}

    {:task "Benchmark and validate"
     :detail
     "Measure frame render time before and after for:
        - j/k navigation on 55 workflows (170x30 terminal)
        - Full view switch (workflow-list → pr-fleet)
        - Overlay toggle (help screen on/off)
      Target: <2ms per navigation frame, <10ms per full rerender."}]

   :acceptance-criteria
   ["Zero intermediate buffer allocations during split-v/split-h/box rendering"
    "All 250 existing tests pass (buffer-based API shim preserves compatibility)"
    "paint-screen! uses array access instead of get-in for cell diffing"
    "Frame render time for j/k navigation is <2ms on 170x30 terminal"
    "Memory allocation per frame reduced by >50% vs current implementation"]}]

 :constraints
 ["Must maintain the Elm architecture contract: view is a pure function of model"
  "Must not break the declarative screens.edn spec format"
  "Must preserve the IScreen protocol — Lanterna and MockScreen both work"
  "Phase 2 and Phase 3 are independent — either can be implemented first"
  "All changes are in tui-engine and tui-views components only"
  "Backward compatibility: old buffer-based tests should still work via shim"]}
